# Diagnostics, paths and symbols

`CompilerDiagnostic` vs `CompilerError`, interned identity and render-boundary ownership.

## Contract

- Input: source locations, symbols, paths and structured reasons from any stage
- Output: typed diagnostics durable across the whole build
- Decides: user-facing diagnostic lanes, string-table identity, render boundaries
- Must not decide: type semantics, AST validation, backend target policy
- Invariant: user failures use `CompilerDiagnostic`: internal and infrastructure failures use `CompilerError`

## Main paths

- `src/compiler_frontend/compiler_messages/`
- `src/compiler_frontend/symbols/`
- `src/compiler_frontend/symbols/interned_path.rs`
- `src/compiler_frontend/paths/`

